    <title>CAPA Tracking - Login</title>
</head>
    <body class="login-body">
        <header class="header-shadow">
            <div class="logout">
                <div class="logo-and-title">
                    <img src="/images/capa-tracking-logo.svg" alt="capa logo">
                    <h1 class="main-header">CAPA Tracker</h1>
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>
        <div class="login-details box-shadow">
            <div class="about-title">
                <img src="/images/capa-tracking-logo-small.svg" alt="capa logo">  
                <h3 class="about-header">CAPA Tracker</h3>  
            </div>
            <p>By <a class="log-in" target="_blank" href="https://coreydamocles.netlify.app/">Corey Damocles</a></p>
            <a href="https://github.com/ubemacapuno" target="_blank"><img class="social"  src="/images/github.svg" alt="capa logo"></a>
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/corey-damocles/" target="_blank"><img class="social" src="/images/linkedin.svg" alt="capa logo"></a>
            <p class="about">Document and track CAPA reports with <span id="capa-tracker">CAPA Tracker</span>! This full-stack application allows users to create CAPA records, add information, update information, and delete entries.</p>
            <p>This application was developed with EJS templating language, HTML/CSS/JavaScript, Node/Express, Passport (Google authentication), and MongoDB. CAPA Tracker is currently a minimal viable product (MVP) and is not production-ready.</p>
            <div class="google-login">
                <a href="/auth/google" class="btn teal lighten-2">
                    <i class="fab fa-google left"></i> Log In With Google
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
